<p><img height="185" width="300" src="http://www.edenhrconsulting.com/images/stories/eden-stick-figures/eden-recruit.jpg" alt="eden-recruit" style="float: right;" />Assessment centres are proven, time and time again, to deliver the best new recruits for your business.  These centres tend to be used mostly for middle and senior managers as, due to the high cost of recruitment, the initial costs are outweighed by the overriding benefits of assessment centres.  Getting the right people in to your business is crucial  to sustain growth and profitability, and has to be a given priority to ensure you are operating a successful business. </p>
<p>Assessment centres are statistically proven to be the optimum form of recruitment practice when evaluating how effective someone will perform in the role that they have been hired for.  Assessment centres are 70% effective, whereas interviewing alone (based on traditional interviewing methods) can be as little as 18% effective.</p>
<p>A recruitment asssessment centre may consist of some of the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Competency or behavioural interviewing</li>
<li>Ability testing – This may be in the form of general numerical/verbal reasoning tests or tests targeted at specific roles e.g. sales, customer service etc.</li>
<li>Personality profiling</li>
<li>Group activities assessing competencies or problem solving skills</li>
<li>Presentation giving on a giving subject (with/without prior notice to the assessment centre)</li>
<li>In-tray exercises</li>
<li>Case study for candidates to analyse</li>
</ul>
<p>Assessment centres are tailored to specific client requiremnets.  Talk to one of our Consultants on how we can develop an assessment centre to get the right candidates for your business.</p>
